https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2F%3Fhprecirc-bullet%5C%22%3EVisit%20INSIDER's%C2%A0homepage%20for%20more%20stories%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20night%20of%20June%2030%2C%201950%2C%20Lt.%20Col.%20Charles%20B.%20Smith%20was%20asleep%20in%20his%20quarters%20at%20Camp%20Woods%20near%20Kumamoto%2C%20Japan%2C%20when%20he%20received%20a%20phone%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lid%20has%20blown%20off.%20Get%20on%20your%20clothes%20and%20report%20to%20the%20CP%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.army.mil%2Fbooks%2Fkorea%2F20-2-1%2FSn06.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20commanding%20officer%20told%20him%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20began%20the%20deployment%20of%20Task%20Force%20Smith%2C%20the%20first%20American%20combat%20troops%20to%20arrive%20and%20fight%20in%20the%20Korean%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20years%20of%20border%20skirmishes%20that%20left%20thousands%20dead%20on%20both%20sides%2C%20the%20North%20Koreans%20launched%20a%20full-scale%20invasion%20against%20the%20south%20on%20June%2025%2C%201950.%20The%20North%20Korean%20army%20was%20well-trained%20and%20well-equipped%20with%20the%20latest%20Soviet%20tanks%20and%20artillery.%20It%20was%20Soviet%20leader%20Josef%20Stalin%20himself%20who%20reluctantly%20gave%20the%20go%20ahead%20to%20North%20Korean%20dictator%20Kim%20Il-Sung%20to%20invade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20South%20Koreans%20were%20in%20no%20position%20to%20effectively%20resist.%20They%20had%20no%20tanks%2C%20little%20artillery%2C%20a%20minuscule%20air%20force%20and%20were%20demoralized%20after%20bloodily%20crushing%20a%20series%20of%20domestic%20uprisings.%20Though%20the%20US%20had%20largely%20exited%20the%20south%20by%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20war%2C%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20had%20built%20North%20Korea's%20army%20into%20a%20fearsome%20instrument.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221182%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%221182px%20%E1%84%91%E1%85%A9%E1%86%A8%E1%84%80%E1%85%A7%E1%86%A8%E1%84%80%E1%85%B5_(7445973890)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5592f5686bb3f77714169e93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%EB%8C%80%ED%95%9C%EB%AF%BC%EA%B5%AD%20%EA%B5%AD%EA%B5%B0%20Republic%20of%20Korea%20Armed%20Forces%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3Cp%3EBombers%20of%20US%20Far%20East%20Air%20Force%20Command%20are%20flying%20in%20formation%2C%201950.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20just%20six%20C-54%20transport%20planes%20available%20for%20airlift%2C%20Smith%20was%20only%20able%20to%20take%20two%20understrength%20infantry%20companies%20with%20a%20skeleton%20headquarters%20and%20a%20weapons%20platoon%20with%20a%20few%20mortars%2C%20obsolete%20bazookas%20and%2075mm%20recoilless%20rifles.%20In%20all%2C%20they%20comprised%20little%20more%20than%20400%20men.%20They%20landed%20in%20Pusan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20July%201%20and%20took%20a%20scratch%20collection%20of%20Korean%20trucks%20and%20civilian%20automobiles%20to%20the%20train%20station.%20Once%20there%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.army.mil%2Fbooks%2Fkorea%2F20-2-1%2FSn06.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmith%20was%20told%20by%20a%20general%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BAll%20we%20need%20is%20some%20men%20out%20there%20who%20won't%20run%20when%20they%20see%20tanks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20train%20ride%20heading%20north%2C%20they%20had%20a%20front%20row%20seat%20to%20the%20chaos%20and%20confusion%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20invasion.%20Four%20Royal%20Australian%20Air%20Force%20fighters%20strafed%20an%20ammunition%20train%20heading%20north%20to%20resupply%20South%20Korean%20soldiers%2C%20blowing%20it%20sky%20high%20and%20killing%20many%20local%20civilians.%20In%20another%20incident%2C%20friendly%20planes%20destroyed%20a%20column%20of%2030%20South%20Korean%20trucks%2C%20killing%20over%20200%20soldiers.%20One%20officer%20present%20observed%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20fly%20boys%20really%20had%20a%20field%20day!%20They%20hit%20friendly%20ammo%20dumps%2C%20gas%20dumps%2C%20the%20Suwon%20air%20strip%2C%20trains%2C%20motor%20columns%2C%20and%20KA%20%5BKorean%20Army%5D%20Hq.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221099%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%221099px%20thumbnail%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5592f6816bb3f79915169e90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Army%20artillery%20crew%20fires%20a%20105%20mm%20howitzer%20against%20North%20Korean%20Communist%20positions%20during%20a%20battle%20in%20the%20Republic%20of%20Korea.%3Cp%3EWikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20linking%20up%20with%20a%20battery%20of%20105mm%20artillery%20that%20had%20just%20arrived%20by%20sea%2C%20Task%20Force%20Smith%20headed%20north%20of%20Osan%20on%20July%204%20to%20scout%20out%20positions%20for%20the%20coming%20battle.%20Their%20mission%20was%20simple%3A%20Delay%20the%20North%20Korean%20advance%20as%20long%20as%20they%20could.%20They%20could%20see%20South%20Korean%20engineers%20wiring%20bridges%20for%20demolition%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20July%205%20at%207%20AM%2C%20with%20the%20soldiers%20dug%20and%20the%20artillery%20positioned%2C%20they%20spotted%20a%20column%20of%20North%20Korean%20tanks.%20Artillery%20called%20in%20against%20them%20proved%20ineffective%2C%20and%20despite%20waiting%20until%20the%20T-34%20tanks%20were%20at%20close%20range%2C%20the%2075mm%20recoilless%20rifles%20couldn't%20penetrate%20their%20armor.%20A%20flurry%20of%20bazooka%20shots%20failed%20to%20penetrate%20as%20well.%20Anti-tank%20mines%20tailored%20for%20the%20situation%20were%20not%20available%20in%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20artillery%20only%20had%20six%20anti-tank%20rounds%2C%20and%20it%20was%20these%20that%20disabled%20two%20enemy%20tanks.%20The%20armor%20came%20in%20waves%2C%20barely%20stopping%20to%20engage%20the%20US%20infantry%20as%20they%20drove%20south.%20After%20they%20passed%2C%20Task%20Force%20Smith%20knew%20that%20enemy%20infantry%20was%20on%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221249%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22M20_75_mm_recoilless_rifle_korean_war%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5592f8b96bb3f7d327169e90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20heavily%20out-gunned%20Task%20Force%20Smith%20had%20only%20M20%2075%20mm%20recoilless%20guns%2C%20bazookas%2C%20and%20precious%20few%20anti-tank%20missiles%20to%20hold%20their%20positions.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20publication%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%20-%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20approaching%20column%20of%20trucks%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.army.mil%2Fbooks%2Fkorea%2F20-2-1%2FSn06.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20estimated%20by%20Smith%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20be%20six%20miles%20long%2C%20with%20three%20tanks%20taking%20the%20lead.%20When%20they%20were%20within%20a%20thousand%20yards%20the%20Americans%20raked%20the%20column%20with%20.50%20caliber%20machine%20guns%2C%20mortars%2C%20and%20artillery.%20Many%20trucks%20were%20destroyed%2C%20and%20enemy%20infantry%20dismounted%20and%20proceeded%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20double%20envelopment%20maneuver.%20Like%20the%20tank%20columns%20before%20them%2C%20they%20seemed%20more%20concerned%20with%20going%20around%20the%20task%20force%20than%20engaging%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20with%20large%20numbers%20of%20the%20enemy%20on%20his%20flanks%20and%20in%20his%20rear%2C%20Smith%20decided%20if%20any%20of%20his%20men%20were%20going%20to%20get%20out%2C%20it%20would%20have%20to%20be%20then.%20Elements%20leapfrogged%20back%2C%20abandoning%20their%20heavy%20weapons%2C%20their%20dead%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20more%20seriously%20wounded.%20A%20medical%20sergeant%20volunteered%20to%20stay%20behind%20with%20them.%20The%20artillery%20spiked%20their%20guns%20upon%20receiving%20the%20word%20to%20withdraw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETask%20Force%20Smith%20suffered%20its%20heaviest%20casualties%20during%20the%20retreat%2C%20with%20enemy%20machine%20gun%20positions%20hitting%20them%20from%20close%20range.%20Elements%20straggled%20back%20into%20Osan%20piecemeal%2C%20with%20some%20scattered%20men%20walking%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20Yellow%20Sea%20and%20the%20Sea%20of%20Japan.%20One%20man%20arrived%20at%20the%20Pusan%20perimeter%20by%20Saipan%20from%20the%20west%20coast.%20In%20all%2C%20Task%20Force%20Smith%20suffered%2042%20killed%20and%2085%20wounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221109%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lossy%20page1%201109px%20Crew_members_of_Company_D%2C_89th_Tank_Battalion%2C_give_first_aid_to_wounded_soldier%2C_during_action_against_the_Chinese..._%20_NARA_%20_531407.tif%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5592f9986bb3f73a3da6e8e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECrew%20members%20give%20first%20aid%20to%20wounded%20soldier%2C%20during%20action%20in%20the%20Korean%20War.%20%3Cp%3EU.S.%20National%20Archives%20and%20Records%20Administration%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20Task%20Force%20Smith%20became%20a%20cautionary%20tale%2C%20to%20the%20point%20that%20upon%20becoming%20Army%20chief%20of%20staff%20in%201991%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Farticles.chicagotribune.com%2F1993-07-27%2Fnews%2F9307270118_1_enemy-tanks-korean-war-task-force-smith%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen.%20Gordon%20Sullivan%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20theme%20as%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20is%20'No%20more%20Task%20Force%20Smiths.'%26quot%3B%20After%20World%20War%20II%2C%20cutbacks%20left%20American%20troops%20poorly%20trained%2C%20under%20equipped%2C%20and%20often%20badly%20understrength.%20The%20Army%20was%20unprepared%20for%20Korea%2C%20and%20the%20soldiers%20paid%20the%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStalin%20had%20resisted%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20North%20invading%20the%20South%20for%20years%20out%20of%20fear%20of%20American%20intervention%2C%20but%20with%20the%20US%20withdrawal%20starting%20in%201948%2C%20the%20situation%20seemed%20changed.%20Stalin%2C%20Communist%20Chinese%20Premier%20Mao%20Zedong%2C%20and%20Kim%20Il-Sung%20assumed%20that%20the%20United%20States%20would%20not%20get%20directly%20involved.%20Stalin%20was%20no%20stranger%20to%20this%20kind%20of%20miscalculation.%20His%20misreading%20of%20his%20erstwhile%20ally%20Adolf%20Hitler%20led%20to%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Ftopics%2Fworld-war-ii%2Foperation-barbarossa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreatest%20geopolitical%20disasters%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20little%20to%20disabuse%20the%20troika%20of%20this%20notion.%20In%20January%201950%2C%20a%20mere%20six%20months%20before%20the%20war%2C%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Dean%20Acheson%20had%20left%20South%20Korea%20out%20of%20the%20US's%20Pacific%20defense%20strategy%20in%20a%20speech%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.lib.unb.ca%2Findex.php%2Fjcs%2Farticle%2Fview%2F366%2F578%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20National%20Press%20Club.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20communists%20interpreted%20this%20doctrine%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bgreen%20light%26quot%3B%20for%20invasion%2C%20and%20anticipated%20a%20quick%20victory.%20They%20were%20badly%20mistaken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%221200px%20Armored_Forces_Memorial_%20_Korea_left_%20_Arlington_National_Cemetery_%20_2011%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5592fa4d6bb3f7013da6e8e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22678%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Armored%20Forces%20Memorial%20at%20Arlington%20National%20Cemetery.%3Cp%3ETim1965%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overwhelming%20strategic%20concern%20%E2%80%94%20far%20exceeding%20the%20fate%20of%20a%20relative%20backwater%20like%20Korea%20%E2%80%94%20lay%20less%20than%20six%20hundred%20miles%20off%20the%20Korean%20coast%3A%20Japan.%20Under%20US%20occupation%20and%20still%20rebuilding%20from%20the%20terrible%20destruction%20of%20World%20War%20II%2C%20Japan%20was%20vital%20to%20US%20military%20power%20in%20the%20Pacific.%20If%20South%20Korea%20fell%2C%20Japan%20would%20face%20a%20grave%20threat%20leaving%20US's%20Pacific%20defense%20strategy%20in%20ruins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20American%20and%20UN%20reinforcements%20arrived%2C%20a%20counteroffensive%20drove%20the%20North%20Korean%20military%20to%20the%20brink%20of%20collapse.%20When%20UN%20forces%20approached%20the%20Yalu%20River%2C%20China%20entered%20the%20war.%20Its%20assault%20sent%20the%20UN%20armies%20reeling%20back%20past%20the%2038th%20parallel%2C%20and%20a%20war%20that%20seemed%20would%20be%20over%20by%20Christmas%20turned%20into%20years%20of%20bloody%20stalemate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20ceasefire%20talks%20had%20begun%20in%20July%201951%2C%20the%20war%20dragged%20on.%20President%20Dwight%20D.%20Eisenhower%2C%20newly%20elected%20in%201952%2C%20decided%20after%20visiting%20Korea%20that%20it%20was%20time%20to%20apply%20enough%20pressure%20to%20force%20a%20peace.%20He%20began%20broadly%20hinting%20in%20public%20statements%20that%20nuclear%20weapons%20might%20be%20used%20if%20a%20ceasefire%20was%20not%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221142%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lossy%20page1%201142px%20Korean_War_Peace_talks._Kaesong%2C_Korea_%20_NARA_%20_292622.tif%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5592faf96bb3f7f03da6e8e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKorean%20War%20Peace%20talks%20in%20Kaesong%2C%20Korea.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20National%20Archives%20and%20Records%20Administration.%20Licensed%20under%20Public%20Domain%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20nuclear%20blackmail%2C%20the%20death%20of%20Stalin%20in%20March%201953%20and%20the%20resulting%20leadership%20shake%20up%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fwgbh%2Famex%2Fbomb%2Fpeopleevents%2FpandeAMEX58.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprobably%20the%20decisive%20factor%20in%20ending%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20carnage%20finally%20ended%20with%20the%20Korean%20Armistice%20Agreement%20on%20July%2027%2C%201953.%20A%20demilitarized%20zone%20was%20established%20separating%20the%20two%20countries%20along%20the%2038th%20parallel%20that%20stands%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20often%20been%20labeled%20the%20%26quot%3BForgotten%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20over%2036%2C000%20Americans%20and%20millions%20of%20Koreans%20and%20Chinese%20died%20in%20a%20conflict%20noted%20for%20its%20utter%20brutality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20US%20strategic%20bombing%20leveling%20most%20of%20North%20Korea%2C%20horrific%20war%20crimes%20committed%20by%20both%20sides%2C%20and%20cities%20changing%20hands%20multiple%20times%2C%20both%20North%20and%20South%20Korea%20were%20devastated.%20It%20ended%20in%20a%20draw.%20But%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.nationalgeographic.com%2Fnews%2F2014%2F02%2F140226-north-korea-satellite-photos-darkness-energy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eif%20satellite%20imagery%20has%20anything%20to%20say%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20South%20Korea%20in%20the%20long%20run%20is%20lucky%20that%20the%20United%20States%20had%20its%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busine