%20U.S.%20CAPITOL%20ATTACK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Attorney%20General%20Merrick%20Garland%20is%20investigating%20Trump's%20role%20in%20actions%20surrounding%20his%20loss%20in%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%20that%20culminated%20in%20Trump's%20supporters'%20deadly%20attack%20on%20the%20U.S.%20Capitol%20on%20Jan.%206%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20said%20his%20attorneys%20met%20on%20Thursday%20with%20U.S.%20Justice%20Department%20officials%2C%20in%20a%20sign%20charges%20could%20come%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20said%20on%20his%20Truth%20Social%20platform%20that%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20had%20not%20told%20his%20attorneys%20when%20action%20was%20likely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20have%20testified%20that%20during%20his%20final%20months%20in%20office%2C%20Trump%20pressured%20them%20with%20false%20voter%20fraud%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20probe%20is%20also%20examining%20a%20plot%20to%20submit%20phony%20slates%20of%20electors%20to%20block%20U.S.%20lawmakers%20from%20certifying%20Biden's%20victory%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EILLEGAL%20RETENTION%20OF%20CLASSIFIED%20DOCUMENTS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20in%20federal%20court%20on%20June%2013%20in%20Miami%20to%20charges%20he%20unlawfully%20kept%20classified%20national%20security%20documents%20when%20he%20left%20office%20in%202021%20and%20lied%20to%20officials%20who%20sought%20to%20recover%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20is%20scheduled%20for%20May%2020%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmith%20accuses%20Trump%20of%20risking%20national%20secrets%20by%20taking%20thousands%20of%20sensitive%20papers%20with%20him%20when%20he%20left%20the%20White%20House%20in%20January%202021%20and%20storing%20them%20in%20a%20haphazard%20manner%20at%20his%20Mar-a-Lago%20Florida%20estate%20and%20his%20New%20Jersey%20golf%20club%2C%20according%20to%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhotos%20included%20in%20the%20indictment%20show%20boxes%20of%20documents%20stored%20on%20a%20ballroom%20stage%2C%20in%20a%20bathroom%20and%20strewn%20across%20a%20storage-room%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20records%20included%20information%20about%20the%20secretive%20U.S.%20nuclear%20program%20and%20potential%20vulnerabilities%20in%20the%20event%20of%20an%20attack%2C%20the%20indictment%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20faces%20charges%20that%20include%20violations%20of%20the%20Espionage%20Act%2C%20which%20criminalizes%20unauthorized%20possession%20of%20defense%20information%2C%20and%20conspiracy%20to%20obstruct%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20prosecutors%20unveiled%20a%20new%20indictment%2C%20which%20charges%20Trump%2C%20his%20co-defendant%20and%20valet%20Walt%20Nauta%2C%20and%20a%20third%20Trump%20employee%2C%20Carlos%20De%20Oliveira%2C%20with%20attempting%20to%20delete%20security%20camera%20footage%20at%20Mar-a-Lago%20after%20they%20were%20sent%20a%20grand%20jury%20subpoena%20for%20the%20videos%20in%20June%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20allege%20De%20Oliveira%20told%20another%20employee%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20boss%26quot%3B%20wanted%20a%20server%20containing%20security%20footage%20to%20be%20deleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGEORGIA%20ELECTION-TAMPERING%20CRIMINAL%20PROBE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFulton%20County%20District%20Attorney%20Fani%20Willis%20is%20investigating%20whether%20Trump%20and%20others%20tried%20illegally%20to%20overturn%20his%20defeat%20in%20that%20state's%202020%20presidential%20vote.%20A%20charging%20decision%20in%20the%20criminal%20case%20is%20expected%20by%20Sept.%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20focuses%20in%20part%20on%20a%20Jan.%202%2C%202021%2C%20phone%20call%20Trump%20made%20to%20Republican%20Georgia%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Brad%20Raffensperger%2C%20asking%20him%20to%20%26quot%3Bfind%26quot%3B%20enough%20votes%20needed%20to%20overturn%20Trump's%20loss%20in%20Georgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20sai