20MOREIRA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%20and%20Chesnot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDustin%20Moskovitz%20said%20Elon%20Musk's%20successful%20companies%20could%20be%20seen%20as%20%26quot%3Bscams%20he%20got%20away%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Facebook%20cofounder%20said%20Musk%20sucked%20up%20resources%20from%20others%20by%20overpromising%20with%20Tesla.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMoskovitz%20pointed%20to%20Musk's%20promises%20on%20autonomous%20cars%2C%20and%20a%20report%20that%20he%20exaggerated%20Tesla%20ranges.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EApparently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-vs-mark-zuckerberg-feud-history-2021-1%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20the%20only%20Facebook%20founder%20that's%20wary%20of%20Elon%20Musk.%20Facebook%20cofounder%20and%20Asana%20CEO%20Dustin%20Moskovitz%20took%20a%20jab%20at%20the%20billionaire%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoskovitz%20said%20people%20often%20argue%20Musk%20makes%20up%20for%20his%20antics%20through%20the%20value%20his%20companies%20Tesla%20and%20SpaceX%20bring%20to%20the%20world%2C%20but%20the%20Asana%20CEO%20said%20he's%20not%20sure%20the%20billionaire's%20success%20is%20legitimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20point%20is%20I%20don't%20really%20see%20these%20companies%20as%20dispensating%20impact%2C%20or%20at%20least%20don't%20give%20nearly%20as%20much%20credit%20to%20him%20as%20others%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Moskovitz%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2F%40moskov%2Fpost%2FCvN_Tt5PdzQ%2F%3Figshid%3DNTc4MTIwNjQ2YQ%253D%253D%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20Threads%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20were%20really%20built%20on%20outward%20lies%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20self-deceptions%20(rose-colored%20glasses)%2C%20then%20we%20should%20really%20see%20them%20as%20scams%20he%20got%20away%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoskovitz%20said%20that%20he%20believes%20Musk%20accelerated%20the%20development%20of%20EVs%20by%20one%20to%20two%20years%20at%20most%20and%20he%20thinks%20the%20Tesla%20CEO%20might%20actually%20have%20delayed%20it%20by%20%26quot%3Boverpromising.%26quot%3B%20Moskovitz%20said%20that%20Musk%20attracted%20customers%2C%20workers%2C%20and%20funding%20through%20his%20lofty%20promises%20for%20EV%20ranges%2C%20as%20well%20as%20autonomous%20driving%20and%20automated%20assembly%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoskovitz%20pointed%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Ftesla-batteries-range%2F%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%20from%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20claimed%20Tesla%2C%20through%20a%20direct%20order%20from%20Musk%2C%20had%20exaggerated%20the%20expected%20range%20for%20its%20EVs%20on%20the%20vehicle's%20dashboard.%20Moskovitz%20added%20that%20the%20higher%20ranges%20made%20Teslas%20%26quot%3Blook%20heads%20and%20tails%20above%20the%20competitors%20and%20that%20was%20not%20true.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20Musk%20nor%20Tesla%20have%20responded%20to%20Reuters'%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReuters%20did%20not%20indicate%20how%20far%20off%20Tesla's%20advertised%20range%20estimates%20were%20from%20its%20actual%20range%2C%20but%20cited%20third-party%20tests%20that%20indicated%20meaningful%20differences%20in%20real-world%20testing.%20The%20electric-car%20maker%20dominates%20the%20US%20market%20in%20large%20part%20because%20legacy%20automakers%20like%20Ford%20and%20General%20Motors%20have%20only%20begun%20to%20scale%20production%20for%20their%20own%20EVs.%20Tesla%20also%20no%20longer%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongest-range-electric-cars-2023-3%232-tesla-model-s-405-miles-20%5C%22%3Elongest%20advertised%20range%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20US%20market%20for%20electric%20cars.%20The%20Lucid%20Air%20has%20a%20range%20of%20about%20516%20miles%2C%20while%20Tesla's%20longest%20range%20vehicle%2C%20the%20Model%20S%2C%20has%20an%20estimated%20range%20of%20about%20405%20miles%20per%20a%20full%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222668%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20white%20Tesla%20Model%20S%20at%20a%20charging%20station%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6365483600d7c60018783dd8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDustin%20Moskovitz%20said%20on%20Threads%20that%20he's%20not%20convinced%20of%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20Musk's%20success.%3Cp%3EBruce%20Bennett%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMoskovitz%20%E2%80%94%20who%20has%20never%20worked%20in%20the%20automotive%20industry%20but%20says%20he%20comes%20at%20the%20issue%20from%20a%20software%20perspective%20%E2%80%94%20said%20that%20Musk's%20%26quot%3Bbig%20promise%26quot%3B%20of%20fully%20autonomous%20cars%20has%20also%20contributed%20to%20the%20company's%20ability%20to%20suck%20up%20resources%20at%20the%20potential%20expense%20of%20competitors.%20The%20Facebook%20cofounder%20pointed%20out%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-history-of-full-self-driving-promise-2022-1%5C%22%3EMusk%20has%20been%20promising%20self-driving%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20years%2C%20but%20the%20carmaker%20still%20only%20offers%20an%20admittedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-full-self-driving-software-fsd-bugs-video-2021-9%5C%22%3Ebuggy%20beta%20version%20of%20FSD%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20requires%20a%20licensed%20driver%20to%20operate%20the%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20work%20in%20software%2C%20I%20get%20that%20delays%20happen.%20But%20these%20are%20*the*%20claims%20that%20positioned%20Tesla%20as%20massively%20ahead%20of%20the%20competition%20and%20created%20a%20belief%20that%20Elon%20can%20pull%20forward%20the%20future%20through%20sheer%20grit%20and%20ingenuity%2C%26quot%3B%20Moskovitz%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20*belief*%20in%20those%20claims%20and%20the%20accelerated%20timelines%20is%20what%20made%20Tesla%20look%20like%20a%20leader%20so%20quickly%3B%20then%20they%20turned%20that%20cache%20into%20actual%20resources%20with%20fundraising.%20Estimating%20correctly%20wouldn't%20have%20looked%20revolutionary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoskovitz%20argued%20that%20Musk%20has%20a%20tendency%20to%20overpromise%20and%20under-deliver%2C%20which%20sucked%20up%20resources%20from%20other%20companies%20like%20BYD%2C%20Toyota%2C%20Nikola%2C%20and%20Rivian.%20It's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20many%20of%20these%20automakers%20did%20not%20start%20making%20EVs%20until%20several%20years%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-cofounder-martin-eberhard-interview-history-elon-musk-ev-market-2023-2%5C%22%3ETesla%20began%20selling%20its%20first%20vehicle%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202008%20after%20the%20company%20was%20founded%20in%202003.%20For%20example%2C%20Chinese%20automaker%20BYD%20didn't%20start%20building%20EVs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FCompanies%2FBYD-Co.-Ltd%5C%22%3Etill%202010%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20EV%20startup%20Nikola%20wasn't%20launched%20until%202014%2C%20and%20Rivian%20wasn't%20founded%20until%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoskovitz%20said%20he%20had%20similar%20thoughts%20regarding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-history-biggest-moments-elon-musk-2022-12%5C%22%3EMusk's%20work%20at%20SpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20company%20that%20is%20privately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F07%2F13%2Felon-musk-spacex-near-150-billion-valuation.html%5C%22%3Evalued%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20about%20%24150%20billion%2C%20but%20said%20he'll%20%26quot%3Btry%20to%20enumerate%20at%20some%20point%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20additional%20comment%20from%20Insider%20ahead%20of%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20agreed%20with%20the%20Facebook%20cofounder's%20hot%20take%20%E2%80%94%20he%20received%20some%20pushback%20from%20users%20in%