-lakh-on-indigo-for-tail-strike-incidents-123072800481_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fdgca-imposes-penalty-of-rs-30-lakh-on-indigo-for-tail-strike-incidents-123072800481_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Without%20Corrections%2C%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20Overseas%20Scholarship%20Could%20Benefit%20Only%20Affluent%20Students%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28125045%2Fimage-1174.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20Rajasthan%20government%20had%20introduced%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20Scholarship%20for%20Academic%20Excellence%20scheme%2C%20with%20an%20objective%20to%20grant%20students%20from%20the%20economically%20disadvantaged%20community%20in%20the%20state%20an%20opportunity%20to%20pursue%20higher%20education%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20scheme%20was%20launched%20on%20the%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20former%20prime%20minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20realising%20his%20vision%20for%20an%20educated%20and%20developed%20India.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20its%20launch%2C%20the%20scheme%20aimed%20to%20help%20200%20students%20from%20the%20state%20to%20pursue%20higher%20education%20at%20prestigious%20institutions%20worldwide%2C%20including%20Oxford%20University%2C%20Harvard%20University%20and%20Stanford%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20comprehensive%20plan%20covered%20financial%20assistance%20for%20students%20pursuing%20undergraduate%2C%20postgraduate%2C%20PhD%2C%20and%20postdoctoral%20studies%2C%20with%20the%20state%20government%20fully%20funding%20the%20expenses%2C%20including%20travel%20fares%20and%20tuition%20fees.%20The%20scholarships%20were%20strategically%20allocated%20across%20various%20disciplines%3A%20150%20scholarships%20were%20designated%20for%20students%20pursuing%20humanities%2C%20social%20science%2C%20agriculture%20and%20forest%20science%2C%20nature%20and%20environmental%20science%2C%20and%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%2025%20scholarships%20were%20granted%20to%20students%20pursuing%20management%20and%20business%20administration%2C%20as%20well%20as%20economics%20and%20finance.%20Lastly%2C%2025%20scholarships%20were%20set%20aside%20for%20students%20studying%20pure%20science%20and%20public%20health%20subjects.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20any%20vacancies%20within%20these%20disciplines%2C%20a%20maximum%20of%2015%20candidates%20could%20be%20awarded%20scholarships%20in%20engineering%2C%20related%20science%2C%20medicine%2C%20and%20applied%20science.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20shortly%20after%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20launch%2C%20significant%20revisions%20were%20made%20to%20the%20guidelines%2C%20which%20allowed%20students%20with%20family%20incomes%20above%20Rs%208%20lakh%20to%20apply%20as%20well.%20These%20revised%20guidelines%20applied%20to%20all%20streams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fforeign-universities-india-govt-indifference%5C%22%3EForeign%20Universities%20Regulations%20Reflect%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Indifference%20to%20Higher%20Education%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20income%20categories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20new%20guidelines%2C%20students%20were%20categorised%20under%20three%20categories%2C%20based%20on%20their%20family%E2%80%99s%20annual%20income%3A%20up%20to%20Rs%208%20lakh%2C%20between%20Rs%208%20lakh%20and%2025%20lakh%2C%20and%20Rs%2025%20lakh%20and%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20modifications%20unfortunately%20led%20to%20misuse%20of%20the%20scheme.%20As%20reported%20by%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20education%20department%20until%20December%202021%2C%20a%20total%20of%20245%20students%20had%20been%20selected%20for%20the%20scholarship%20scheme%2C%20with%2073%20of%20them%20being%20children%20of%20government%20employees%2C%20including%2014%20IAS%20and%20IPS%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20most%20of%20the%20beneficiaries%20belonged%20to%20the%20two%20new%20income%20categories%20that%20were%20recently%20introduced.%20The%20primary%20objective%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20as%20emphasised%20by%20chief%20minister%20Ashok%20Gehlot%2C%20during%20its%20launch%2C%20was%20to%20provide%20students%20from%20the%20economically%20weaker%20sections%20access%20to%20150%20leading%20global%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20purpose%20appears%20to%20have%20lost%20its%20essence%20with%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20new%20income%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudents%20falling%20within%20the%20income%20bracket%20of%20Rs%208%20lakh%20to%2025%20lakh%20or%20those%20above%20Rs%2025%20lakh%20per%20annum%20could%20feasibly%20afford%20admission%20and%20other%20related%20costs%20on%20their%20own%2C%20making%20them%20less%20in%20need%20of%20support%20from%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20concrete%20action%20taken%20by%20the%20government%20to%20investigate%20the%20selection%20process%20that%20resulted%20in%20the%20inclusion%20of%2073%20students%20with%20government%20servant%20parents%20in%20the%20scheme%20is%20concerning.%20This%20lack%20of%20scrutiny%20gives%20rise%20to%20questions%20about%20the%20transparency%20and%20fairness%20of%20the%20selection%20procedure.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20to%20broaden%20the%20income%20criteria%20for%20the%20scheme%20appears%20to%20be%20flawed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20the%20government%20responsibility%20to%20ensure%20proper%20advertising%20and%20widespread%20dissemination%20of%20information%20about%20the%20scheme%20to%20all%20eligible%20students.%20This%20is%20because%20those%20falling%20within%20the%20lower%20income%20brackets%20might%20not%20have%20equal%20access%20to%20information%20compared%20to%20those%20belonging%20to%20the%20higher%20income%20categories.%3Cins%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F26163735%2F2022_9img25_Sep_2022_PTI09_25_2022_000119B-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22749%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F26163735%2F2022_9img25_Sep_2022_PTI09_25_2022_000119B-1.jpg%20749w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F26163735%2F2022_9img25_Sep_2022_PTI09_25_2022_000119B-1-300x181.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-621336%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22453%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAshok%20Gehlot.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20issues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202023-24%20budget%2C%20the%20government%20increased%20the%20scholarship%20seats%20in%20this%20scheme%20from%20200%20to%20500%20per%20year%2C%20but%20regrettably%2C%20they%20have%20not%20revised%20their%20stance%20on%20the%20income%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20concerning%20provision%20in%20the%20scheme%20is%20that%20if%20a%20selected%20candidate%20gets%20a%20job%20during%20the%20course%E2%80%99s%20duration%2C%20their%20scholarship%20will%20be%20revoked%2C%20and%20the%20money%20will%20be%20reclaimed.%20This%20provision%20is%20fundamentally%20flawed%2C%20as%20many%20foreign%20countries%20have%20traditions%20of%20allowing%20part-time%20jobs%20for%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20preventing%20students%20from%20engaging%20in%20part-time%20work%2C%20India-bound%20students%20might%20face%20difficulties%20in%20sustaining%20themselves%20in%20a%20foreign%20country%20with%20a%20higher%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20while%20managing%20their%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPart-time%20work%20offers%20valuable%20experiences%2C%20exposing%20students%20to%20the%20culture%20and%20traditions%20of%20the%20host%20country%2C%20which%20can%20be%20an%20invaluable%20asset%20to%20their%20personal%20growth%20and%20development.%20However%2C%20this%20aspect%20has%20seemingly%20been%20disregarded%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20true%20fulfillment%20of%20the%20late%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20vision%20and%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20objectives%20will%20only%20be%20achieved%20when%20it%20prioritises%20economically%20weaker%20individuals%20instead%20of%20assisting%20students%20from%20families%20with%20a%20gross%20income%20exceeding%20Rs%2025%20lakh%20per%20year.%20To%20increase%20awareness%20and%20participation%2C%20the%20local%20education%20department%20can%20conduct%20sessions%20in%20both%20government%20and%20private%20schools%20to%20inform%20students%20about%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20benefits%20and%20application%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20to%20encourage%20students%20belonging%20to%20economically%20disadvantaged%20families%2C%20the%20scheme%20can%20directly%20select%20toppers%20of%20the%20Senior%20Secondary%20School%20Board%20examinations%20from%20the%20poor%20sections%20without%20relying%20on%20a%20lottery%20system.%20This%20approach%20would%20serve%20as%20an%20incentive%20and%20inspire%20more%20students%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20timely%20corrections%20to%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20shortcomings%2C%20there%20is%20a%20risk%20that%20only%20affluent%20students%20will%20benefit%20from%20it.%20To%20avoid%20such%20disparity%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20address%20the%20loopholes%20promptly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBhuvnesh%20Kumar%20and%20Sharad%20Panwar%20are%20fourth%20year%20law%20students%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20University%2C%20Jodhpur.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690540242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28125045%2Fimage-1174.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire