me-court.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F07%2F17%2Fthe-limits-of-institutional-independence-the-supreme-courts-ed-director-judgment%2F%5C%22%3Eprevious%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20recent%20judgment%20involving%20the%20tenure%20extensions%20granted%20to%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%2C%20I%20had%20wondered%20%E2%80%93%20somewhat%20rhetorically%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20have%20any%20respect%20for%20itself%2C%20and%20for%20its%20own%20orders%3F%E2%80%9D%20The%20context%20for%20this%20was%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20found%20that%20the%20ED%20director%20had%20been%20kept%20in%20his%20role%2C%20in%20flagrant%20breach%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20own%20orders%2C%20for%20a%20period%20of%20one%20year%20and%20eight%20months%3B%20but%20far%20from%20visiting%20any%20consequences%20upon%20the%20executive%2C%20the%20SC%20allowed%20the%20director%20to%20%3Cem%3Estay%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20his%20role%20until%20the%20end%20of%20July%2C%20to%20facilitate%20%E2%80%9Ca%20smooth%20transition.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20light%20of%20fresh%20events%2C%20one%20must%20now%20not%20only%20wonder%20whether%20the%20SC%20has%20any%20respect%20for%20itself%20and%20its%20own%20orders%2C%20but%20whether%20it%20has%20respect%20for%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20In%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20judgment%2C%20the%20executive%20filed%20an%20application%20asking%20for%20an%20%3Cem%3Eextension%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20the%20ED%20director%20until%20the%20end%20of%20October%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20his%20input%20was%20needed%20for%20the%20global%20FATF%20review.%20Notice%20the%20breathtaking%20audacity%20here%3A%20far%20from%20being%20chastened%20by%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20holding%20that%20it%20had%20breached%20a%20direct%20order%20not%20once%2C%20but%20twice%20(in%20granting%20the%20ED%20director%20two%20extensions)%2C%20the%20executive%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20sanction%20a%20%3Cem%3Efurther%20%3C%2Fem%3Eextension%20of%20a%20continuing%20illegality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20would%20think%20that%2C%20in%20a%20jurisdiction%20that%20is%20formally%20committed%20to%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20and%20to%20the%20principle%20that%20government%20is%20not%20above%20the%20law%2C%20such%20an%20application%20would%20not%20only%20be%20dismissed%2C%20but%20that%20punitive%20costs%20would%20be%20imposed%20upon%20the%20executive%20for%20wasting%20judicial%20time%20(after%20all%2C%20the%20judiciary%20has%20been%20quite%20eager%20of%20late%20to%20impose%20costs%20on%20petitioners%20for%20wasting%20its%20time).%20One%20would%20be%20wrong.%20After%20a%20brief%20hearing%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20sanctioned%20a%20further%20extension%20to%20the%20ED%20directors%E2%80%99%20tenure%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20public%20interest%E2%80%9D%2C%20until%20the%20middle%20of%20September%20(half%20the%20time%20the%20executive%20had%20asked%20for%20%E2%80%93%20as%20if%20what%20was%20happening%20was%20a%20negotiation%20for%20a%20salary%20increment%2C%20and%20not%20a%20serious%20issue%20involving%20the%20rule%20of%20law).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20today%20sent%20a%20signal%20that%20in%20India%2C%20there%20is%20one%20entity%20%E2%80%93%20and%20one%20entity%20alone%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20entitled%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20its%20own%20wrong%2C%20not%20once%2C%20not%20twice%2C%20but%20many%20times%20over%3B%20and%20that%20there%20is%20only%20one%20entity%20that%20can%20refuse%20to%20comply%20with%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20order%2C%20and%20not%20only%20get%20away%20with%20it%2C%20but%20benefit%20from%20it.%20That%20entity%20is%20the%20Union%20government.%20One%20would%20be%20hard-pressed%20to%20imagine%20a%20more%20destructive%20or%20damaging%20undermining%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20consequences%20follow.%20One%20is%20that%20Thursday%E2%80%99s%20order%20will%20only%20further%20embolden%20the%20executive%20to%20treat%20the%20constitution%20and%20the%20law%20as%20optional.%20Because%20not%20only%20are%20there%20no%20judicial%20sanctions%20for%20breach%2C%20breach%20is%20actively%20%3Cem%3Eincentivised.%20%3C%2Fem%3EIn%20such%20a%20circumstance%2C%20who%20would%20%3Cem%3Enot%20%3C%2Fem%3Etake%20advantage%20of%20the%20impunity%20that%20has%20been%20so%20generously%20offered%3F%20Wouldn%E2%80%99t%20you%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20is%20a%20more%20long-term%20consequence%2C%20although%20as%20troubling.%20If%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20unable%20%E2%80%93%20or%20unwilling%20%E2%80%93%20to%20enforce%20its%20own%20previous%2C%20direct%20orders%20(not%20once%2C%20not%20twice%2C%20but%20%3Cem%3Emany%20%3C%2Fem%3Etimes)%20in%20the%20face%20of%20executive%20recalcitrance%2C%20then%20what%20hope%20%E2%80%93%20if%20any%20%E2%80%93%20ought%20citizens%20to%20have%20in%20its%20ability%20or%20willingness%20to%20adjudicate%20cases%20involving%20serious%20and%20far-reaching%20constitutional%20breaches%20by%20the%20executive%3F%20Would%20not%20such%20cases%20and%20constitutional%20challenges%20be%20effectively%20turned%20into%20a%20formality%2C%20where%20the%20outcome%20is%20known%2C%20and%20everyone%20simply%20goes%20through%20the%20motions%3F%20We%20are%20aware%20of%20jurisdictions%20where%20that%20is%20the%20case%3B%20and%20unfortunately%2C%20orders%20such%20as%20today%E2%80%99s%20raise%20a%20disquieting%20sense%20of%20proximity.%20After%20all%2C%20as%20a%20senior%20counsel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frethinkaadhaar.in%2Fblog%2F2017%2F5%2F4%2Fsenior-advocate-datar-aadhaar-is-like-building-a-bridge-and-then-looking-for-a-river-it-is-hunting-for-problems-to-make-itself-relevant%5C%22%3Eonce%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20court%20%E2%80%93%20in%20what%20seems%20an%20eternity%20ago%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cas%20nightfall%20does%20not%20come%20at%20once%2C%20neither%20does%20oppression.%20In%20both%20instances%2C%20there%20is%20a%20twilight%20when%20everything%20remains%20seemingly%20unchanged.%20And%20it%20is%20in%20such%20twilight%20that%20we%20all%20must%20be%20most%20aware%20of%20change%20in%20the%20air.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F07%2F27%2Fthe-ed-director-judgment-ii-the-supreme-court-against-the-rule-of-law%2F%5C%22%3Eauthor%E2%80%99s%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20republished%20with%20permission.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fgautam-bhatia%5C%22%3EGautam%20Bhatia%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690531812000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28133058%2Fsk-mishra-supreme-court.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fed-director-extension-supreme-court-respect-rule-of-law%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20extended%20S.K.%20Mishra's%20tenure%20until%20the%20middle%20of%20September%20at%20the%20executive's%20request.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20court%20has%20sent%20a%20signal%20that%20in%20India%2C%20there%20is%20one%20entity%20%E2%80%93%20and%20one%20entity%20alone%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20entitled%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20its%20own%20wrong%2C%20not%20once%2C%20not%20twice%2C%20but%20many%20times%20over.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A70%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fed-director-extension-supreme-court-respect-rule-of-law%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20firms%20can%20go%20for%20listing%20on%20foreign%20exchanges%2C%20IFSC%3A%20Sitharaman%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690531613000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-07%2F16%2Ffull%2F1689505600-99